ðŸ“Œ  Jenkinsfile Practical Work & Assignments

1. Install Java (JDK 17)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y
java -version
# Roman Urdu: Java install karo, Jenkins aur Maven ke liye zaroori hai

2. Install Maven
sudo apt install maven -y
mvn -v
# Roman Urdu: Maven install karo, project build aur dependency management ke liye

3. Install Jenkins
wget -q -O - https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian/jenkins.io-2023.key | sudo apt-key add -
sudo sh -c 'echo deb https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian binary/ > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list'
sudo apt update
sudo apt install jenkins -y
# Roman Urdu: Jenkins server install karo, ye CI/CD ke liye use hoga

4. Start & Enable Jenkins Service
sudo systemctl start jenkins
sudo systemctl enable jenkins
sudo systemctl status jenkins
# Roman Urdu: Jenkins ko start karo aur enable karo system startup ke liye

5. Access Jenkins Dashboard
http://<your-server-ip>:8080
# Roman Urdu: Browser mein Jenkins dashboard open karo

6. Install Node.js & npm
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nodejs -y
sudo apt install npm -y
node -v
npm -v
# Roman Urdu: Node.js aur npm install karo project run aur build ke liye

7. Project Folder Setup
mkdir my-node-app
cd my-node-app
npm init -y
# Roman Urdu: Naya Node.js project banao ya existing folder open karo

8. Create Jenkinsfile
nano Jenkinsfile
# Roman Urdu: Jenkinsfile create karo project root mein, pipeline define karne ke liye

9. Jenkinsfile Content (Declarative Pipeline)
pipeline {
  agent any

  stages {
    stage('Install Dependencies') {
      steps {
        sh 'npm install'
      }
    }

    stage('Run Tests') {
      steps {
        sh 'npm test'
      }
    }

    stage('Build') {
      steps {
        sh 'npm run build'
      }
    }

    stage('Deploy') {
      steps {
        echo 'Deploying the application...'
      }
    }
  }
}
# Roman Urdu: 4 stages define ki: install, test, build, deploy

10. Setup pom.xml (Maven dependencies)
nano pom.xml
# Roman Urdu: Maven project ka pom.xml setup karo dependencies aur build ke liye

11. Setup package.json (Dummy scripts)
nano package.json
# Paste provided content
# Roman Urdu: Node.js scripts define karo test aur build simulation ke liye

12. Push Project to GitHub
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/shan376/node-ci-pipeline.git
git add .
git commit -m "Initial Maven project with Jenkinsfile"
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
# Roman Urdu: Project GitHub pe push karo, Jenkins repo se connect karne ke liye

13. Add GitHub Credentials in Jenkins
Jenkins â†’ Manage Jenkins â†’ Credentials â†’ (Global) â†’ Add Credentials
# Roman Urdu: Jenkins mein GitHub credentials add karo

14. Create Jenkins Pipeline Job
Jenkins Dashboard â†’ New Item â†’ Name: node-ci-pipeline â†’ Pipeline â†’ OK
Pipeline section: Pipeline script from SCM, Git, Repository URL, Branch: */main, Script Path: Jenkinsfile
# Roman Urdu: Jenkins pipeline job create karo aur GitHub repo link karo

15. Setup Webhook in GitHub
Repo â†’ Settings â†’ Webhooks â†’ Add Webhook â†’ Payload URL: http://<jenkins-ip>:8080/github-webhook/ â†’ Content type: application/json â†’ Event: push
# Roman Urdu: GitHub se Jenkins ko auto trigger ke liye webhook setup karo

16. Enable GitHub Trigger in Jenkins
Pipeline Job â†’ Configure â†’ Build Triggers â†’ Check "GitHub hook trigger for GITScm polling"
# Roman Urdu: Jenkins pipeline automatic run ke liye trigger enable karo

17. Real-time Testing
README.md, index.js ya Jenkinsfile edit karo â†’ GitHub pe push karo
# Roman Urdu: Har push pe Jenkins automatically build, test aur deploy simulate karega

